Hi @jobert, yes that appears to be the case. I just tested it again, and it does depend on the network and can be a bit hit-or-miss. 

But from the request/response timings what I can gather is that "groups" of requests were processed in parallel (rows 0 to 3 were processed at the same time, then rows 4 to 7, etc.) and locking might not be implemented between each worker or something like that.

